The paper proposes a framework that leverages deep neural networks for active learning on attributed graphs. This involves graph embedding and semi-supervised learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of informativeness measures and query strategies, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses graph data and attributes, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
